<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-05-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-05-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="477" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d477">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 865.111/15</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Jay</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-05-06">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 6, 1916</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>634. Referring to the Embassy’s number 633, May 4. Permanent
                            Undersecretary of State informed me this evening that matter was
                            receiving very sympathetic consideration of the Foreign Office and other
                            departments and that he felt certain that some arrangement will be
                            effected within the next few days by which in practice, even if not
                            officially, wives and children will be permitted to leave. I received
                            distinct impression Foreign Office most anxious to arrange this matter
                            so as to avoid any ill feeling or irritation in the United States.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Jay</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>